  "text": "We expect that the network will learn different cue invariances depending on the task and categories it is trained on. For example, it may choose to focus on just the texture cue when detecting leopards, and not their shape or context, as their texture is unique. To evaluate the effect of task-specific pre-training, we compare three different variants of the network: 1) one pre-trained on the generic ImageNet [CITATION_1] ILSVRC 1000-way classification task (IMGNET); 2) the same network additionally fine-tuned on the PAS-CAL 20-category detection task (PASC-FT); and 3) for the case when a category has no or few labels, we fine-tune the IMGNET network on synthetic CAD data (VCNN).",
